headline: 1 Growth Stock Down 38% to Buy Right Now
summary: Several top chip stocks have surged to new highs recently, but Advanced Micro Devices (NASDAQ: AMD) has trailed the pack.  Revenue from data centers grew 122% year over year in Q3, driven by strong sales of AMD's EPYC central processing units (CPUs) and Instinct graphics process units (GPUs).  EPYC has become a popular CPU for data centers due to its ability to deliver competitive performance while driving down the cost of ownership.
